tip.text: Awesome food, quick service. Loved the squid ink & prawn risotto and the crab meat pasta! Will definitely be back
A fantastic restaurant! Food was delicious. Must try the seafood  antipasto platter, roasted cod and the choc lava cake!
Great service, nice ambience and very cute 3D coffee art
Kouigm Amann and Salted Caramel Cruffin was perfect. A must have!
Average food, slow service, inattentive staff. Prawn mee had more chicken in it than prawns.  Better off at BLab or La Casa
Cute little cafe. Lemon meringue tart was amazing. Smoothie bowl was a treat too
Really cosy place to eat and unwind. Love the old-school interior. The Bistro Tang Laksa and the Nyonya Chicken Curry were good!
Delicious cendol! A great refreshment to keep you going in the Penang heat. Fresh, generous portions and cheap.
Pulled pork was nice, French toast wasn't the best but still had nice flavours. Passion fruit & mint cooler could have been better if they used real passionfruit.
Delicious, smooth and silky. Nicely blended.

formattedAddress: Lot 130, Solok Kampung Bahagia, Klebang Besar (Jalan Klebang Besar)
location.address: Lot 130, Solok Kampung Bahagia, Klebang Besar

tip.text: Thai milk tea and Thai green tea was delightfully refreshing. Air fried bread was different, but the Thai Kaya dip was a little bit tasteless.
Prawn mee was pretty good, would definitely go back. Recommend the 3 in 1 (Prawn, ribs, tail) or standard Prawn mee.
White sauce pizza was so-so, coffee was below average. Probably could find more authentic pizza elsewhere...
Salted caramel pancakes with peanut butter crumbs was a delight to have. The dirt cake was a cute idea, but the cake itself was pretty average.
Heisenburger with sweet potato fries was juicy and tasty. Also recommend the grilled chicken with lychee and sweet chilli sauce.
Curry fries were tasty but the burgers were a bit cold. The Har Jeong Kai burger had a lot of flavour, but too salty. Super Burger was bland. Saving grace: The Nutella crepe cake.
Don't understand the long lines for this place. The iced coffe & Beef Slice Pho was average, not the most flavoursome.  For an authentic experience, try Pho 99 - highly recommend it!

formattedAddress: B1-131, Suntec City Mall (3 Temasek Boulevard, #)

tip.text: Truffle fries were reallllllly good! Eggs bennies and French toast were average. Side of fruits on the french toast was too sour.
Awesome cafe, great food and even better coffee. Must try the Artistry Chilli Crab Burger and the PB&J French Toast- delicious!
Chef's recommendation- Chicken cutlet curry omlette rice and Baked cheese with Tomato and chicken rice was nice, worth a try!
Simple little coffee shop that sells amazing Pho and Vietnamese rolls. Best I've had in SG
Top notch Cambodian restaurant- delicious food and superb service. Try the Bamboo shoot & smoke soup and the Takeo Sausages.
Great place for Khmer/Western fusion tapas. Recommend the Burmese chicken curry with crispy noodles & Coconut beetroot salad.
Great to see amazing Khmer artifacts, but if you're not into all that, probably would suggest giving it a miss.
Favourite place for a feed, amazing restaurant with great service. Try the fish amok, chicken vege curry and tiger prawns- delicious!
A beautiful palace- worth spending a few hours to explore the grounds. Take time to really absorb the serenity of this place.
Really enjoyed the Summer Barra Chirashi and Ox Tounge Rice Bowl. Finish with the green tea creme brulee and dont forget to try the red or white juice. Delicious!
The signature coconut ice cream, so refreshing and delicious. Top it off with peanuts
Recommend the pesto chicken toast with orange, but sadly all the toasts were a bit cold and coffee was weak. General ambience quite nice and relaxing.
Delicious food and great service. Loved the rib eye, cooked to perfection. The angel hair aglio olio with tiger prawns was also impressive.
Just another new fad. Mediocre ice cream, but the breakfast and the Himalaya Salted ice cream (minus the layer of cotton candy) were the tastier ones. Get in earlier to grab a seat.
Mee Siam, top hat, curry laksa...simple nyonya food in a nice, cosy set up. Worth a visit!
B Lab Club sandwhich was fresh and tasty! Coffee was also decent. But the smoked duck baguette was too hard and quiet unpleasant to eat; overall the service was really slow.
One of the tastiest Curry Laksa I've had. Impressive serving of seafood too. Dont forget to ask for extra salmon!
Pleasantly impressed with the food. Decent Spanish tapas. Aubergine chips, roasted lamb and the 'special paella' were some highlights

formattedAddress: Publika (Lot G2.34, Block C5), Jalan Dutamas 1
location.address: Publika (Lot G2.34, Block C5), Jalan Dutamas 1

tip.text: Loved the Mojito Malaya, and the Asamboi Margarita is also worth a try. Cosy place!
Try the pulled chicken & breakfast Gnocchi, was nice & tasty. A very pleasing brunch spot!

formattedAddress: A4-G2-7, Solaris Dutamas,  No 1, Jalan Dutamas 1
location.address: A4-G2-7, Solaris Dutamas,  No 1, Jalan Dutamas 1

tip.text: Smoked duck salad & Royal Saumon was so-so & not worth the $$. Would just stick to ordering coffee and cakes here. But really friendly and fast service.

formattedAddress: 72, Jalan Burhanuddin Helmi (Taman Tun Dr. Ismail)

tip.text: Nice ambience, pad Thai was really good and also try the lychee mint drink! Yum!
Ribs & Dirty Duck were very average. Portion sizes were standard. Probably better off going elsewhere
Coffee was pretty good. The aubergine and portobello mushroom salad was a bit disappointing for my liking
Big breakfast was pretty sad and kofta meatballs with spaghetti was average. Green tea latte was too milky, very unpleasant. Overall, disappointing.

formattedAddress: 15, Lorong Rahim Kajai 13 (Taman Tun Dr. Ismail)

tip.text: The chunky mushroom pie was average. Golden soft shell crab spaghettini is so nice- a must try.
Burger @ Sentral is so delicious and juicy! A must have. Lobster Mac & Cheese is also nice, but could do with more lobster

formattedAddress: Lobby Level, Le Méridien Kuala Lumpur (2 Jalan Stesen Sentral)
location.address: Lobby Level, Le Méridien Kuala Lumpur

tip.text: Tried two of the 'Most Popular' dishes- The Ang Moh was mediocre, presentation could've been much better. But the Norwegian was okay.
Chicken chop was decent. Miso Cod & Quinoa was also nice. Overall, a satisfying meal.
The spicy macaroni beef soup & nasi ulam with chicken curry was average. Great ambience though, would come back to try their desserts!
Ambience was nice. Expected great things from this place but very dissapointed with the service- food came out slow, waiters mixing up orders and it wasnt even busy.
Beef lasagne was quite tasty. Zero thirst juice is always a favourite of mine. Definitely coming back!

formattedAddress: Bangsar Village II, Bangsar (Jalan Telawi 3, Bangsar Baru)

tip.text: Energy lift drink was delicious! Also try the lui cha and rainbow salad
Wolf's fave pasta and pork burger was good! Finish off with the Minty fresh juice.

contact.facebookName: Three Little Pigs & the Big Bad Wolf

venue.name: Three Little Pigs & The Big Bad Wolf

tip.text: Tasty nasi lema- the beef rendang and fried chicken quite nice. Just a little overpriced.
*Must try- Teochew Olive Rice, hometown tofu, poached baby spinach with century and salted egg, samsui ginger chicken
Wild mushroom quiche was quitr good, pineapple freeze and apple/elderflower drink nice and refreshing. Dad's curry laksa was very dissapointing,  tasteless. Seafood vermicelli soup was bland.
